---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { ROUTES } from '../data/siteRoutes'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Shuswap Commons"
  description="Learn what Shuswap Commons is, why it exists, and how it helps people find current local information."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="breadcrumbs">
          <a href={ROUTES.home}>Home</a>
          <span>›</span>
          <span>About</span>
        </div>

        <h1>Built for clearer local discovery.</h1>

        <p>
          Shuswap Commons is a curated local directory for finding businesses,
          services, makers, recreation, stays, and community resources across
          the Shuswap.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="wrapper content-section about-grid">
      <article id="mission" class="content-panel glass">
        <p class="kicker">Our mission</p>

        <h2>Make useful local information easier to find.</h2>

        <p>
          Local information often gets scattered across aging directories,
          social feeds, tourism pages, and business websites. Shuswap Commons
          brings the useful pieces together in a cleaner, more current format.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article id="how-it-works" class="content-panel glass">
        <p class="kicker">How it works</p>

        <h2>Curated first, automated later.</h2>

        <p>
          Listings are organized by category, area, freshness signals, and
          practical details. The first version uses carefully structured mock
          data while the frontend is refined before Sanity CMS is connected.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article id="community-updates" class="content-panel glass">
        <p class="kicker">Community updates</p>

        <h2>A future home for local notices.</h2>

        <p>
          The directory can later support community updates, seasonal resources,
          events, volunteer needs, local notices, and practical information for
          residents and visitors.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article id="resources" class="content-panel glass">
        <p class="kicker">Resources</p>

        <h2>For residents, visitors, and businesses.</h2>

        <p>
          This project is designed to support people looking for reliable local
          services while also giving businesses a clearer place to be found and
          kept up to date.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="wrapper cta">
      <div>
        <h2>Have something to add?</h2>

        <p>
          Send a business, correction, or useful local resource through the
          submission page.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a class="btn amber" href={ROUTES.submit}>
          Submit an Update

          <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <use href="#i-arrow" />
          </svg>
        </a>

        <a class="btn" href={ROUTES.directory}>
          Browse Directory

          <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <use href="#i-arrow" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>